From Stephen Guerke Subject Re How can I use the mouse in NON Windows applications under MS WINDOWS In article gonzaled LGV MC writes One addition to I don't know if it applies to For my Microsoft mouse to work with windowed DOS apps I had to use the driver that came with Windows Version didn't allow me to do it for some For Logitech rodents use the lmouse driver that comes with also you need to be using a video driver that supports use of the mouse both the VGA and SUPERVGA that come with Windows will support both of these are color drivers if you're lucky the manufacturer of your video card might have a driver that is compatable and will support a Steve Stephen Guerke Computer Resources University of Delaware Parallel Program Georgetown DE